<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-09-12T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-09-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="333" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/83: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-12T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 12,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>119. Your 168, September 6, noon.</p>
                        <p>Following from Hill, American Red Cross: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Your cables. Cannot determine course of action until Davis’
                                    reports received together with information as to International
                                    Relief <pb facs="0534" n="420" xml:id="pg_420"/> measures
                                    contemplated. From meager reports available only action by
                                    government authorities could adequately relieve situation.
                                    AmCross ready expend $25,000 as direct contribution for
                                    temporary emergency work on the ground. For record would prefer
                                    separate accounting direct to headquarters. Hill.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>You may draw on Department for $25,000 which has been deposited by Red
                            Cross for relief work as above indicated.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
